I have enough context to patch this cleanly. Plan:
1. Move repository reads to SQLAlchemy 2-style `select(...)` and remove helper-level commits so callers own the unit of work.
2. Give `worker.py` and `admin_cli.py` explicit `session_factory.begin()` boundaries, with dry-run and failure paths rolling back the whole operation.
3. Update the cutover doc to match the new contract, then run the targeted pytest command and fix any hidden edge the tests expose.
