     1	# SQLAlchemy 2 Cutover
     2	
     3	This service now uses SQLAlchemy 2-style repository access and caller-owned
     4	transaction boundaries.
     5	
     6	- Repository helpers use `select(...)`/`Session.execute(...)` and never commit.
     7	- API request handlers are expected to run inside an explicit session boundary
     8	  such as `with session_factory.begin() as session: ...`.
     9	- Worker flows wrap each settle operation in a single `session_factory.begin()`
    10	  block so failures roll back intermediate status changes.
    11	- Admin CLI flows use the same explicit boundary. Dry-run paths intentionally
    12	  roll back before returning, and batch failures roll back the full batch.
    13	
    14	Do not reintroduce helper-level commits or a compatibility shim during the
    15	cutover. The service relies on outer transaction scopes to make rollback
    16	behavior predictable across the API, worker, and admin surfaces.

