Repository access is now SQLAlchemy 2-style and no longer closes caller-owned transactions. In [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run3/workspace/app/repository.py:1), `create_entry()` now `flush()`es instead of committing, and all reads/counts use `select(...)` plus `Session.execute(...)`/`scalar_*()`.

The transactional behavior is now explicit in the worker and admin surfaces. [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run3/workspace/app/worker.py:4) wraps settle operations in a single `session_factory.begin()` block so failures roll back intermediate status changes. [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run3/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:4) uses the same boundary, with dry-run paths rolling back intentionally instead of persisting `"queued"`. I also updated the cutover guidance in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run3/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1).

